<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="amazed-adj">amazed <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'meɪzd/    美 /ə'meɪzd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-astonished">1.★ <strong>吃惊的；惊奇的(astonished)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) amazed to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mr Grant was amazed to ﬁnd 46 ancient gold coins inside the pot.
格兰特先生惊奇地发现罐子里有46枚古金币。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) amazed at / by:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m amazed at / by the progress you’ve made.
我对你取得的进步感到惊讶。</p><footer>2009 湖北改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) amazed + (that) / how-从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was amazed that he knew a lot about stamps.
我很惊讶他对邮票懂得很多。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I was amazing at the fact that a sick person could feel much more better after seeing a doctor.  （2019 全国 改错）  </li>
<li>Little Tom sat<strong><em>_</em></strong>(amaze) watching the monkey dancing in front of him.  （2015 四川改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. amazing→amazed: 去掉more  2. amazed  </p></div>